{"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/michellegroth/practicing-vectors-mini-mini-project?scriptVersionId=102626664\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown","outputs":[],"execution_count":0},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"10ea651e","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005308,"end_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.077678","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.07237","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["----\n","6th August 2022\n","----"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"85264372","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005969,"end_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.087691","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.081722","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["# Mood in July \n","\n","Data type: numeric \n","\n","Data source: CSV table exported from Daylio, a mood tracking app. \n","\n","## Data Cleaning & Preparation \n","\n","I opened the table in Google Sheets. The table contained the following data: full date, date, weekday, time, mood, activties, and notes. The mood was recorded as the following characters: depressed, bad, meh, good, and rad. \n","\n","In order to perform calculations on this data, I assigned a numeric values from 1-5 to each of the moods, 1 being \"depressed\", and 5 being \"rad\". The assignment of values was carried out using the following function: \n","\n","``` \n","=IF(E2=\"depressed\",1,IF(E2=\"bad\",2,IF(E2=\"meh\",3,IF(E2=\"good\",4,IF(E2=\"rad\",5)))))\n","```\n","\n","On some days, more than one mood was recorded in a day. For the sake of this little practice project, I simplified things by using the mood that was last in each day, deleting the other entries for that day. \n","\n","I froze the title row of the sheet so that it wouldn't be affected by sorting and organising. I then sorted the sheet by date, in ascending order and used a thick border to mark out and make it easier to see where each week started and ended. Four weeks were marked out from the 4th to the 10th, the 11th to the 17th, the 18th to the 24th and the 25th to the 31st. \n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"3e4379c9","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003918,"end_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.095461","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.091543","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## Creating & Naming Vectors"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"id":"eb38e726","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.107374Z","iopub.status.busy":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.105499Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.253523Z","shell.execute_reply":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.247437Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.156366,"end_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.255882","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.099516","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["# creating vectors\n","\n","week_1 <- c(4, 4, 3, 4, 4, 2, 3)\n","\n","week_2 <- c(4, 4, 3, 3, 4, 4, 3)\n","\n","week_3 <- c(4, 2, 2, 3, 3, 2, 1)\n","\n","week_4 <- c(3, 4, 4, 4, 3, 4, 4)\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"919a88c3","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.29369Z","iopub.status.busy":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.264887Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.312176Z","shell.execute_reply":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.310518Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.054819,"end_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.314559","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.25974","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["# naming vectors\n","\n","daysoftheweek <- c(\"Monday\", \"Tuesday\", \"Wednesday\", \"Thursday\", \"Friday\", \"Saturday\", \"Sunday\")\n","\n","names(week_1) <- daysoftheweek\n","names(week_2) <- daysoftheweek\n","names(week_3) <- daysoftheweek\n","names(week_4) <- daysoftheweek\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"12640e95","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003787,"end_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.322367","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.31858","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## Questions & Calculations\n","\n","1. What was my average mood for each week?\n","2. Which week was my mood highest? \n","3. Which week was my mood lowest? \n","4. What was my average mood across all four weeks? \n","5. On average, which day of the week is my mood highest? \n","6. On average? which day of the week is my mood lowest?  "]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"4f709b0e","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.336419Z","iopub.status.busy":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.335047Z","iopub.status.idle":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.367616Z","shell.execute_reply":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.366086Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.043746,"end_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.369693","exception":false,"start_time":"2022-08-05T23:57:06.325947","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":["<style>\n",".dl-inline {width: auto; margin:0; padding: 0}\n",".dl-inline>dt, .dl-inline>dd {float: none; width: auto; display: inline-block}\n",".dl-inline>dt::after {content: \":\\0020\"; padding-right: .5ex}\n",".dl-inline>dt:not(:first-of-type) {padding-left: .5ex}\n","</style><dl class=dl-inline><dt>Monday</dt><dd>4</dd><dt>Tuesday</dt><dd>4</dd><dt>Wednesday</dt><dd>3</dd><dt>Thursday</dt><dd>4</dd><dt>Friday</dt><dd>4</dd><dt>Saturday</dt><dd>2</dd><dt>Sunday</dt><dd>3</dd></dl>\n"],"text/latex":["\\begin{description*}\n","\\item[Monday] 4\n","\\item[Tuesday] 4\n","\\item[Wednesday] 3\n","\\item[Thursday] 4\n","\\item[Friday] 4\n","\\item[Saturday] 2\n","\\item[Sunday] 3\n","\\end{description*}\n"],"text/markdown":["Monday\n",":   4Tuesday\n",":   4Wednesday\n",":   3Thursday\n",":   4Friday\n",":   4Saturday\n",":   2Sunday\n",":   3\n","\n"],"text/plain":["   Monday   Tuesday Wednesday  Thursday    Friday  Saturday    Sunday \n","        4         4         3         4         4         2         3 "]},"metadata":{},"output_type